{
  "texts": [
    "Contemporary studies use ω = 0.8 GeV [73].",
    "Then, with ωD = (0.94 GeV) 3 and renormalisation point invariant current quark masses (in GeV) mu = md = 0.0055, ms = 0.14, (14) corresponding to ms / mu = 25.5, one obtains (in GeV):m π = 0.135, f π = 0.095, m K = 0.495, f K = 0.116,(15)i.e., values in line with experiment [74].",
    "(Here, minor differences in comparisons with Ref.",
    "[73] owe to omission of the [1/ ln]-tail therein.)",
    "Typically, if the product ωD is kept fixed, physical observables remain practically unchanged under ω → (1 ± 0.2)ω [39]."
  ]
}